<li id="cite_note-9"><b><a href="#cite_ref-9" title="">^</a></b> <a href="/wiki/Anne_Dacier" title="Anne Dacier">Anne Dacier</a>'s translations, 1699 and 1708, turned Homer's verses into prose and generated an uproar among European intellectuals, who were surprised about the archaic tone they showed.</li>
